java.util.concurrent/ScheduledExecutorSe.description:
Submits a periodic action that becomes enabled first after the
given initial delay, and subsequently with the given period;
that is, executions will commence afterinitialDelay, theninitialDelay + period, theninitialDelay + 2 * period, and so on.

